  2,197,"ňĻCommitment toňļ pilgrimage is made in appointed months.¬†Whoever commits to ňĻperformingňļ pilgrimage, let them stay away from intimate relations, foul language, and arguments during pilgrimage. Whatever good you do, God ňĻfullyňļ knows of it. Take ňĻnecessaryňļ provisions ňĻfor the journeyňļ‚ÄĒsurely the best provision is righteousness. And be mindful of Me, O people of reason"
  2,198,"There is no blame on you for seeking the bounty of your Lord ňĻduring this journeyňļ.¬†When you return from ‚ÄôAraf√Ęt,¬†praise God near the sacred place¬†and praise Him for having guided you, for surely before this ňĻguidanceňļ you were astray"
